        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ethan_a/{size}/1383_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-02-13T12:14:13.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Just opened my first bottle of 16. The nose definitely has an interesting savory and herbaceous element that I didn\u2019t find in the 15 or 14, i guess this is from the botryris? On the palate it has a lot more acidic cut than the 15 but is fuller bodied than the 14. Very good  It paired well with a light chicken dish.</p>",
